      "content": "thanks, the numpy version is way faster. \n\nbut i just ran a test on the chip and the score is still a bit low because the sensor data is sometimes noisy. we need a higher score to pass the final gates. \n\nif we can't make the math faster, can we just simplify the logic to get the latency down even more? like, is there a way to make it even lighter so the score jumps? i don't mind if it's a bit less precise as long as the efficiency ratio looks good for the demo.",
